## Limitations

This report primarily focuses on the positive aspects of social media use among teens, as highlighted by the selected sources. It does not extensively cover the negative impacts, such as cyberbullying or addiction, which are also significant concerns. Additionally, the rapidly evolving nature of social media platforms means that findings can quickly become outdated. Further research is needed to continuously assess the long-term effects of social media on teen mental health and development.

